column10:
The only game I pre-ordered on steam, because I knew I would enjoy it. 
- Coop experience is superb, almost on par with Borderlands :P 
- Great price!
- Devs are continuously adding new content, either in form of DLCs or new modes for the game;
- Modded realm, for community made mods;
- Skaven, Chaos and Beastmen! Creating very dynamic challenges on the battlefield;
- Besides weekly modes and modded realm, you can challenge yourself with Deeds (added stipulations to existing maps), Twitch integration (great tool for streamers to include their chat, and was available on release); 
- New weapon types keep coming, and the latest ones are more unique than ever;
- 20 different 'classes' to choose from, and they all play differently;
- Skill trees that impact how you play the character quite a bit. 
- Great idle dialogues. Great lore of an already vast world, and immersive characters!


Downsides are common glitches or bugs that might ruin the immersion; replayability lies in grinding the missions over and over again, for epic loot and skins (and some skins are just glowing beginner skins). Mission maps are less linear than in Vermintide 1, but still a linear experience when it comes to level design and what to expect. Enemies and loot are what's very dynamic. 

Edit: With Chaos Wastes (rogue-lite) &  Weaves addon modes, and who knows what other content in the future, the game has much more replayability now.

[b] Overall a great game for it's price, and you can enjoy the paid DLCs if anyone you are playing with owns them (they can host it for you). [/b]

Daily routine of a WV2 player:
07:00: Wake up;
07:05: Slay some rakies for morning training;
09:00: Go rant about Sienna not having a 4th career yet;
10:30: Slay some more rakies;
13:30: Exchange some slurs with Kerillian;
14:40: Slay even more rakies with your newly gathered anger;
17:15: Eat your healthy dose of magnesium, cause you will need it, if you play with Hunter in party;
17:30:  You do something that involves the rakies again;
20:05: Study some Khazalid to understand what is Bardin blabbering about;
20:15: Final push on the rakies with some dwarven songs to sing along to; 
22:30: Go to bed feeling fulfilled for the day.

10/10 Would recommend to anyone!
